.TH WINETOP 1 "July 2026" "winetop 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
winetop \- htop for Wine prefixes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B winetop
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B winetop
\fICOMMAND\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
winetop discovers Wine/Proton-related processes, groups them into sessions
(Steam AppId, Lutris, Heroic, Bottles, or plain WINEPREFIX), shows resource
usage, and stops the right unit safely.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list
Print sessions as a table (or JSON with \fB--json\fR).
.TP
.B tree
Print a process tree of Wine-related PIDs.
.TP
.B orphans
List lonely wineservers, zombies, and leftover sessions.
.TP
.B status
Emit a single-session snapshot for status bars. Default format is Waybar JSON.
Uses a double CPU sample (\fB--sample-ms\fR, default 250). Pick policy:
\fBhottest\fR (default), \fBrss\fR, or \fBfocused\fR (Sway/Hyprland window hints).
.TP
.B kill
Stop a process (\fB--pid\fR), Steam game (\fB--appid\fR), prefix (\fB--prefix\fR),
or session id (\fB--session\fR).
.TP
.B dump
Write a full JSON snapshot to stdout.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-refresh\-ms \fIN\fR
TUI refresh interval (default 1000).
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Debug logging on stderr.
.SH TUI KEYS
See winetop help screen (\fB?\fR) for the full keymap.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wineserver (1),
.BR wine (1)
.SH BUGS
https://github.com/akovari/winetop/issues
